    <section class="mb-5">
        <h2>The Evolution of Field Hockey Sticks</h2>
        <p>
            Field hockey sticks have come a long way from their humble beginnings. Originally crafted from wood, early sticks were durable but lacked versatility. Modern advancements in material science have introduced composite sticks made from carbon fiber, fiberglass, and aramid, revolutionizing the sport.
        </p>
        <img src="/_content/Hockeyshop.SharedViews/content/img_sticksTechnology/evolution-of-hockey-sticks.jpg" alt="Evolution of Field Hockey Sticks" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm my-3">
        <p>
            Today’s composite sticks offer a perfect balance of power, control, and durability. They are lighter than wooden sticks and allow players to generate more power while maintaining precision during play.
        </p>
    </section>

