    <section class="mb-5">
        <h2>The Manufacturing Process</h2>
        <p>The creation of composite field hockey sticks involves several precise steps to ensure quality and performance:</p>

        <ul class="list-group mb-3">
            <li class="list-group-item"><strong>1. Prepreg:</strong> Carbon fiber sheets are impregnated with resin to form strong, flexible layers.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item"><strong>2. Lay-up:</strong> Sheets are layered in specific patterns to optimize strength and stiffness.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item"><strong>3. Moulding:</strong> The stick is shaped under high pressure and heat to achieve the desired profile.</li>
            <li class="list-group-item"><strong>4. Finishing:</strong> The stick is sanded, painted, and coated for durability and aesthetics.</li>
        </ul>

        <img src="/_content/Hockeyshop.SharedViews/content/img_sticksTechnology/manufacturing-process.webp" alt="Manufacturing Process" class="img-fluid rounded shadow-sm my-3">

        <p>This meticulous process ensures that each stick meets the demands of modern field hockey players, offering both power and precision.</p>
    </section>

    <section class="mb-5">
        <h2>Choosing the Right Stick</h2>
        <p>The choice of a field hockey stick depends on your playing style and preferences:</p>

        <table class="table table-bordered table-hover bg-light shadow-sm text-center">
            <thead class="table-dark">
